<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's the secret to being a successful evil RPer. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
RPing evil seriously all the time will only get you burnt out and bored with it. But role playing evil to the effect that you are occasionally goofy and laughable....that's where the fun is.  In other words, learning to &quot;ham it up&quot; is the best part of role playing. <br>
<br>
My evil characters tend to be like that. They are boastful, arrogant, delusional and conceited megalomaniacs.... yet they are also very vulnerable, insecure, bumbling, self-evident putzes that you just can't help yourself to laugh at them sometimes.... <br>
<br>
and deep down inside, one starts to wonder if such personnas are really genuinely evil.... or simply unloved and misunderstood? <br>
<br>
This is what I like about role playing.... it doesn't have to be one-dimensional. It never has to be linear. Even the example of &quot;evil&quot; role playing does not have a single perfect template. <br>
<br>
--<br>
Moandor T'Varis<br>
Torturer of small cute animals<br>
Sex symbol of Neriak <br>
<br>
&quot;Doubt leads to fear, fear leads to anger, anger leads to suffering, and suffering leads to..... muffins....mmmm, I think I smell muffins!&quot; <br>
